      "justification_correct": "Per CFE Manual 2024, effective mobile surveillance in urban settings requires five to six investigators to maintain coverage through turns, traffic lights, and subject counter-surveillance attempts. This allows for vehicle rotation, leap-frogging techniques, and parallel positioning while minimizing detection risk.",
      "justification_wrong": "One or two investigators are easily detected and lose subjects during routine traffic. Three to four may suffice in rural settings but prove inadequate in complex urban environments where multiple vehicles and positioning options are essential per surveillance best practices.",
