    {
      "num": 4,
      "text": "When conducting surveillance as part of a fraud investigation, which action would MOST likely expose the investigator to civil liability?",
      "tag": "Surveillance - Legal Considerations",
      "options": [
        "A. Recording a conversation in a public place where subjects have no reasonable expectation of privacy",
        "B. Photographing a subject's activities visible from a public street without trespassing",
