        "D. Observing and documenting the subject's business activities during normal operating hours"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "CFE Manual 2024 emphasizes GPS tracking personal property without authorization violates privacy rights and potentially criminal statutes in many jurisdictions. United States v. Jones established warrant requirements for GPS tracking. Private investigators face civil liability for trespass to chattels, invasion of privacy, and potential criminal charges.",
      "justification_wrong": "Activities in public spaces where privacy expectations don't exist are generally permissible. Observations from lawful vantage points and recording where no privacy exists are acceptable investigative techniques. GPS tracking uniquely involves physical intrusion and monitoring beyond public observation, creating distinct legal exposure.",
      "difficulty": "STANDARD",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "fraud_investigation/quiz_001_en.json"
